          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**Lower-left rosette with figures.** A complex circle showing what appear to be small standing figures arranged around a patterned central disk. Unlike the other rosettes on this folio, this one carries embedded human forms — a feature it shares with the balneological quire, which has led to the hypothesis that the rosettes summarise content distributed elsewhere in the manuscript.",
